# API Routes

## Structure

Every route in `app/api/[name]/route.ts`:

1. `createClient()` from `@/utils/supabase/server` — cookie-aware auth
2. `getUser()` — return `401` if missing
3. Zod `safeParse` on body — return `400` with `details` on failure
4. Ownership check on campaign/brand rows — `403` / `404`
5. `try/catch` — explicit HTTP status + `{ success: false, error: "..." }`

## Limits & billing

Use `assertAiRateLimit`, `assertCampaignLimit`, `consume_credit` from `utils/usage-limits.ts` and `utils/plan-limits.ts`. Return `LIMIT_EXCEEDED` with `tier` and `upgradeUrl` when capped.

## AI routes

- Gemini: structured JSON via `responseMimeType: "application/json"` + Zod parse
- Fal: queue + webhook at `/api/webhooks/fal`; client listens via Supabase Realtime + 5s polling fallback
- TTS: server-only ElevenLabs; never expose API keys to client

## Example error shape

```json
{ "success": false, "error": "Human-readable message", "code": "LIMIT_EXCEEDED" }
```
